## Overview

In 2022, Barrett [sent](https://www.freep.com/story/news/politics/elections/2022/05/04/abortion-roe-v-wade-supreme-court-leak/9628831002/) campaign mailers that said he was “100%” opposed to abortion with “no exceptions.” He said he [opposed exceptions for rape and incest](https://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/local/michigan/2022/05/25/abortion-michigan-swing-races-us-house-roe-v-wade-rape-incest-life-of-mother/9853004002/). In 2022, Barrett also [claimed](https://heartlandsignal.com/2024/08/05/audio-shows-that-gop-congressional-candidate-tom-barrett-opposes-rape-incest-exceptions-for-abortion-bans/) that women used abortion as a form of birth control. He has also previously [suggested](https://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/local/michigan/2022/05/25/abortion-michigan-swing-races-us-house-roe-v-wade-rape-incest-life-of-mother/9853004002/) that the would consider federal legislation to restrict abortion access. While in the Michigan state legislature he [supported](https://www.legislature.mi.gov/Bills/Bill?ObjectName=2019-SB-0357&QueryID=162578566) legislation that would ban abortion after approximately six weeks and introduced an [abortion ban](https://www.thedailybeast.com/gop-candidates-stop-worrying-and-embrace-hard-line-rhetoric-on-abortion) opposed by Michigan doctors that did not include exceptions for rape or incest. In 2018, Barrett [suggested](https://www.facebook.com/watch/?ref=search&v=10156451641772708&external_log_id=4cfd9c02-2ae7-4911-ac1c-396431e95b62&q=%22tom%20barrett%22) he would support legislation that designated a fetus as a tax dependent. 

-   [Barrett](https://www.facebook.com/watch/?ref=search&v=10156451641772708&external_log_id=4cfd9c02-2ae7-4911-ac1c-396431e95b62&q=%22tom%20barrett%22): “Any way in which we can acknowledge the fact that a pregnancy and an unborn child is a human being, and is a child that’s fully participating and fully protected by our laws is something that I would encourage and support.”

Barrett opposed Roe v. Wade and called the Dobbs decision an anti-choice [“call to action.”](https://x.com/tombarrettmi7/status/1540384893636677639) He has also [described himself](https://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/local/michigan/2022/05/25/abortion-michigan-swing-races-us-house-roe-v-wade-rape-incest-life-of-mother/9853004002/) as an anti-choice leader. Barrett [volunteered](https://heartlandsignal.com/2024/08/05/audio-shows-that-gop-congressional-candidate-tom-barrett-opposes-rape-incest-exceptions-for-abortion-bans/) at so-called “crisis pregnancy centers,” which doctors have said mislead and endanger women with [misinformation](https://www.acog.org/advocacy/abortion-is-essential/trending-issues/issue-brief-crisis-pregnancy-centers) that can delay them from accessing appropriate care. 

## Barrett Said He Was “100-Percent Pro Life—No Exceptions” And Supported Abortion Bans 

### **Barrett Opposed Abortion “100%” With “No Exceptions”**

**_2022: Barrett Said He Was “100% Pro Life—No Exceptions”_**

**2022: Barrett Sent Fundraising Flyers Saying He Was “100% PRO-LIFE – NO EXCEPTIONS.”** According to the Detroit Free Press, "State Sen. Tom Barrett, R-Charlotte, who is in a tough race to try to knock off U.S. Rep. Elissa Slotkin, D-Holly, in a toss-up district that includes Lansing, has been sending out fundraising flyers calling himself ‘100% PRO-LIFE — NO EXCEPTIONS.’" \[Detroit Free Press, [5/4/22](https://www.freep.com/story/news/politics/elections/2022/05/04/abortion-roe-v-wade-supreme-court-leak/9628831002/)\]

**_2022: Barrett Said He Opposed Abortion Exceptions For Rape And Incest_** 

**May 2022: Barrett Said He Opposed Abortion Exceptions For Rape Or Incest.** According to the Detroit News, "Barrett confirmed he doesn't favor exceptions in cases of rape or incest but said in an interview that preserving the life of the mother is important: ‘I consider pro-life to be pro-life for the mother, as well.’" \[Detroit News, [5/25/22](https://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/local/michigan/2022/05/25/abortion-michigan-swing-races-us-house-roe-v-wade-rape-incest-life-of-mother/9853004002/)\]

-   **Barrett: “No One Is Defending \[Rape\]. This Is Simply A Fundamental Recognition That Human Life Is Worth Protecting, Especially The Most Vulnerable.”** According to the Detroit News, "Barrett confirmed he doesn't favor exceptions in cases of rape or incest but said in an interview that preserving the life of the mother is important: ‘I consider pro-life to be pro-life for the mother, as well.’ ‘Rape is a terrible, terrible offense. No one is defending that,’ Barrett said. ‘This is simply a fundamental recognition that human life is worth protecting, especially the most vulnerable.’"  \[Detroit News, [5/25/22](https://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/local/michigan/2022/05/25/abortion-michigan-swing-races-us-house-roe-v-wade-rape-incest-life-of-mother/9853004002/)\]

**_2024: Barrett Claimed Federal Involvement In Abortion Should Be In Support Of The Hyde Amendment, Parental Consent And Conscience Rights_**

**October 2024: Barrett Claimed He Would Not Support A Federal Abortion Ban But Would Work To Protect The Hyde Amendment, Conscience Rights, And Parental Consent.** According to the Detroit News, "When asked whether he would support a potential federal ban on abortion, Barrett said he believed that fell outside of congressional authority. ‘I’m not going to vote for something that is outside the scope of authority of the United States Congress,’ Barrett said. But Barrett said he would work at the federal level to protect the Hyde Amendment, which prevents federal funding from going toward abortions; protect rights of conscience for medical providers who decline to aid in an abortion; and ensure minors can’t be transported across state lines for an abortion without a parent’s permission. He also wants to decrease cost hurdles for adoption." \[Detroit News, [10/5/24](https://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/politics/2024/10/05/michigan-congress-tom-barrett-curtis-hertel-illegal-immigration-border-abortion-tax-incentives-evs/75351287007/)\]

Barrett added that he sees Congress' role as ensuring federal funds aren't used for abortions and that doctors aren't forced to perform the procedure in violation of their own consciences." \[Detroit Free Press, [9/9/24](https://www.freep.com/story/news/politics/elections/2024/09/09/barrett-hertel-us-house-race-michigan/75069362007/)\]

What are your thoughts on that? Would you support somebody being able to write them off or count them as a dependent? BARRETT: Sure. I think any way in which we can acknowledge the fact that a pregnancy and an unborn child is a is a human being, and is a child that's, you know, fully participating and fully protected by our laws is something that I would encourage and support. I'm very pro-life. It's something that is deeply fundamental to my belief system. And a major reason why I'm involved in public policy is because I believe that we need to do a better job of protecting human life at all vulnerable stages, and in particular the life of the unborn. And whatever we can do to add encouragement to more, step forward from a point of view in a public policy role to encourage more women to keep their pregnancies, I think is something we should do. And it goes a way toward acknowledging this value on human life that we put on our society.” \[Facebook, Michigan Family Forum, [3/23/18](https://www.facebook.com/watch/?ref=search&v=10156451641772708&external_log_id=4cfd9c02-2ae7-4911-ac1c-396431e95b62&q=%22tom%20barrett%22)\] (video) 00:02:21-00:03:34

### Barrett Volunteered At So-Called “Crisis Pregnancy Centers,” Which Were Known to Provide Misinformation to Women

**_Barrett Said He Volunteered At “Crisis Pregnancy Centers,” Which Doctors Said Endangered Women By “Misinterpreting And Misrepresenting Medical Advice”_** 

**2022: Barrett Said He Volunteered At “Crisis Pregnancy Centers.”** According to the Heartland Signal, "Barrett went on to explain that he volunteers at pregnancy crisis centers with his wife. Crisis pregnancy centers are widely notorious for pretending to be medial clinics and spreading medical disinformation in order to intercept women that might get an abortion." \[Heartland Signal, [8/5/24](https://heartlandsignal.com/2024/08/05/audio-shows-that-gop-congressional-candidate-tom-barrett-opposes-rape-incest-exceptions-for-abortion-bans/)\]

-   **HEADLINE: "Why Crisis Pregnancy Centers Are Legal But Unethical"** \[American Medical Association Journal Of Ethics, Drs. Amy G. Bryant and Jonas J. Swartz, [March 2018](https://journalofethics.ama-assn.org/article/why-crisis-pregnancy-centers-are-legal-unethical/2018-03)\]
-   **American Medical Association Published An Article Explaining How “Crisis Pregnancy Centers” Endangered Women By “Misinterpreting And Misrepresenting Medical Evidence.”** According to an article in the American Medical Association Journal of Ethics by Drs. Amy G. Bryant and Jonas J. Swartz, "Nonmaleficence, or the idea that health care professionals should ‘do no harm,’ is violated in multiple ways by CPCs. First, because these centers might tell women they have ‘plenty of time’ to get an abortion, they could delay access to abortion, which could lead to women missing the gestational age cut-off for abortion in a given state; expose women to more involved and slightly riskier procedures at higher gestational ages; or cause women to miss the opportunity for abortion altogether \[8\]. Second, false or misleading information about contraception, condoms, and abortion could lead to unnecessary anxiety or failure to use measures that protect against sexually transmitted infections \[24\].  From a public health standpoint, these centers endanger women by misinterpreting and misrepresenting medical evidence. States implicitly endorse these centers when they provide support for them. Women are put in a difficult position when they have to navigate a perplexing landscape: abortion is safe and legal in every state, yet some states support and promote centers that provide inaccurate information on abortion. These conflicting messages presume a level of sophistication on the part of patients—that they understand the political landscape that underlies the abortion debate and that they are able to make informed, autonomous decisions despite the misinformation that they are given \[11\]. "\[American Medical Association Journal Of Ethics, Drs. Amy G. Bryant and Jonas J. Swartz, [March 2018](https://journalofethics.ama-assn.org/article/why-crisis-pregnancy-centers-are-legal-unethical/2018-03)\]
-   **The American College Of Obstetricians And Gynecologists Said “Crisis Pregnancy Centers” Represented Themselves As Legitimate Reproductive Health Clinics, But “Actually Aim To Dissuade People From Accessing Certain Types Of Reproductive Health Care.”** According to the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, "CPC is a term used to refer to certain facilities that represent themselves as legitimate reproductive health care clinics providing care for pregnant people but actually aim to dissuade people from accessing certain types of reproductive health care, including abortion care and even contraceptive options." \[American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, Issue Brief, Viewed [9/4/24](https://www.acog.org/advocacy/abortion-is-essential/trending-issues/issue-brief-crisis-pregnancy-centers)\]
-   **The American College Of Obstetricians And Gynecologists Said “Crisis Pregnancy Centers” “Use False And Misleading Information, Emotional Manipulation, And Delays To Divert Pregnant People From Accessing Comprehensive And Timely Care From Patient-Centered, Appropriately Trained, And Licensed Medical Professionals."** According to the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, "Abortion is a safe medical intervention backed by decades of robust data. Despite this fact, many CPC staffs use false and misleading information, emotional manipulation, and delays to divert pregnant people from accessing comprehensive and timely care from patient-centered, appropriately trained, and licensed medical professionals." \[American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists, Issue Brief, Viewed [9/4/24](https://www.acog.org/advocacy/abortion-is-essential/trending-issues/issue-brief-crisis-pregnancy-centers)\]

#### October 2024: Barrett Supported Federal Funding For So-Called “Crisis Pregnancy Centers”

**October 2024: Barrett Said His Focus Would Be On Supporting The Hyde Amendment And Providing Government Funding To So-Called “Crisis Pregnancy Centers.”** According to Michigan Advance, "While Barrett said he would not support a national abortion ban, he noted his focus on protecting the Hyde Amendment, which bans the use of federal funding for abortion with exceptions for pregnancies that endanger the life of the pregnant person or that result from rape or incest. \[…\] Barrett’s campaign previously told the Advance he would also focus on ensuring nonprofit crisis pregnancy centers continue to receive government funding." \[Michigan Advance, [10/10/24](https://michiganadvance.com/2024/10/10/in-mid-michigan-congressional-race-hertel-and-barrett-center-pitches-around-the-middle-class/)\]

#### August 2022: Barrett Claimed He Did Not Know Why The Anti-Abortion Section Of His Website Was Removed And Said “I Am Sure We Probably Were Updating Things Based On The Issues That Were Most Salient Right Now”

**August 2022: Barrett Claimed He Did Not Know Why The Anti-Abortion Section Of His Website Was Removed And Said “I Am Sure We Probably Were Updating Things Based On The Issues That Were Most Salient Right Now.”** According to the Detroit News, "Republican congressional candidate and state Sen. Tom Barrett has removed the ‘values’ section of his campaign website that touted his anti-abortion position and history with the pro-life movement. Barrett told The Detroit News on Friday that he's not changed his anti-abortion position. He's still opposed to abortion and supports no exceptions in cases of rape or incest. He didn't know why the website was changed but noted that it's always being updated. ‘I don't watch my own website every day, so I don't know,’ Barrett said. ‘But I am sure we probably were updating things based upon the issues that were most salient right now, which are inflation, cost of living, crime, border security. Those are really the four pillars that are the leading issues that voters are most concerned with.’" \[Detroit News, [8/27/22](https://www.detroitnews.com/story/news/politics/2022/08/27/insider-top-michigan-democrats-may-not-need-debate-gop-opponents-lawmaker-suggests/7903424001/)\]

### October 2024: Barrett Said He Had No Policy On In Vitro Fertilization And Contraception

**October 2024: Barrett Said He Had No Policy On In Vitro Fertilization And Contraception.** According to Michigan Advance, "However, Barrett told the Advance he would not support a national abortion ban, as he feels it falls outside of Congress’s authority. ‘I don’t support things that are outside of the authority of Congress and I don’t believe that a federal abortion ban is within the authority of the scope of what Congress can do,’ Barrett said. Barrett also said he has no policy on in vitro fertilization and contraception, accusing Hertel and his opponents of employing ‘scare tactics.’" \[Michigan Advance, [10/10/24](https://michiganadvance.com/2024/10/10/in-mid-michigan-congressional-race-hertel-and-barrett-center-pitches-around-the-middle-class/)\]
